laboratory_examinations.findings: GRAM POSITIVE COCCI IN PAIRS AND CLUSTERS.

Dependent bibasilar atelectasis, mild ground-glass opacities, hyperemia surrounding the gallbladder fossa, small amount of residual fluid, patent hepatic and portal veins, normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenals, kidneys enhancing symmetrically, right kidney in pelvic position, free intraperitoneal air consistent with recent open cholecystectomy.
